"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754593","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-06","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given to him on 10 February 2016 to Question 26707.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-06T16:03:20.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754593/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754593/answer","Hansard Extract 10 February 2016.docx","Hansard Extract 10 February 2016.docx","RAF Northolt","RAF Northolt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754593/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-20","RAF Northolt: Aviation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether RAF service personnel have been involved in the marketing and promotion of commercial flights at RAF Northolt.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","6524"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754594","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-08","<p>The Ministry of Defence awards thousands of contracts each year, with expenditure against each closely monitored by the relevant Project Team. Information about these is published in the Trade Industry &amp; Contracts Statistical Bulletin which is available at the following link:</p><p>http://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/mod-trade-industry-and-contracts-2016</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-09-08T13:35:30.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754594/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754594/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754594/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-20","Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many defence procurement contracts went over budget in (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012, (d) 2013, (e) 2014, (f) 2015, (g) 2016 and (h) 2017.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","6500"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754595","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-06","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my hon. Friend the then Minister of State for Defence Procurement (Mr Phillip Dunne) on 22 February 2016 to Question 26707.</p><p>One Ministry of Defence civil servant at Executive Officer grade is employed at RAF Northolt with a salary range of £24,663 to £28,253. There are five personnel employed through the multi-activity contractor, within the Commercial Booking Cell. I am withholding these staff costs as they are commercially sensitive.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","6523","2017-09-06T16:06:24.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754595/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754595/answer","Hansard 22 February 2016 26707.docx","Hansard 22 February 2016 26707.docx","26707 - WQnA extract on RAF Northolt","26707 - WQnA extract on RAF Northolt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754595/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-20","RAF Northolt: Aviation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether RAF service personnel are involved in providing services for commercial flights at RAF Northolt.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","6522"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754596","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-06","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my hon. Friend the then Minister of State for Defence Procurement (Mr Phillip Dunne) on 22 February 2016 to Question 26707.</p><p>One Ministry of Defence civil servant at Executive Officer grade is employed at RAF Northolt with a salary range of £24,663 to £28,253. There are five personnel employed through the multi-activity contractor, within the Commercial Booking Cell. I am withholding these staff costs as they are commercially sensitive.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","6522","2017-09-06T16:06:24.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754596/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754596/answer","Hansard 22 February 2016 26707.docx","Hansard 22 February 2016 26707.docx","26707 - WQnA extract on RAF Northolt","26707 - WQnA extract on RAF Northolt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754596/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-20","RAF Northolt: Aviation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many non-military staff are employed at RAF Northolt for the purposes of providing services for commercial flights; and how much the provision of such staff costs.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","6523"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754597","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>Income received from the use of RAF Northolt for commercial aviation for the last financial year is given below:</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>Commercial Aviation (£ million)</p></td><td><p>Aviation Leases (£ million)</p></td><td><p>Total income (£ million)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>8.6</p></td><td><p>0.2</p></td><td><p>8.8</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-09-05T14:56:38.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754597/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754597/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754597/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-20","RAF Northolt: Aviation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much is received in payment for the use of RAF Northolt for commercial flights.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","6521"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754598","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>As the only level one partner on F-35, we have been working closely with the US from the outset of the Programme. We have also been working through the UK/US Statement of Intent on Carrier Co-operation which has ensured continuity of our skills. Most recently, under these arrangements the UK Secretary of State for Defence and the US Secretary of Defense announced that USMC F-35B aircraft would embark in HMS QUEEN ELIZABETH's first operational deployment in 2021. This will be the subject of more detailed planning over the coming years. We will continue to identify opportunities to develop interoperability with our allies in the future.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-09-05T15:06:27.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754598/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754598/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754598/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-20","Aircraft Carriers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans are in place to establish a joint US-UK experimental aircraft carrier force unit.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","6346"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754599","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>Our thoughts continue to be with Corrie McKeague's family at this very difficult time. Primacy remains with the civilian police. However, Ministry of Defence officials have remained engaged with the civilian police throughout the search for Corrie and will continue to provide appropriate support and assistance.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-09-05T14:05:00.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754599/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754599/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754599/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-20","Corrie McKeague","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will provide an update on the search for the missing RAF serviceman Corrie McKeague.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","6375"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754600","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>No assessment has been made by the Department of the suitability for house building on military sites in the City of York, this is a matter for any potential new purchaser in conjunction with the Local Planning Authority. In accordance with standard procedure, a Land Quality Assessment will be undertaken by the Department prior to any sale.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-05T14:13:08.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754600/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754600/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754600/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-20","Military Bases: York","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment his Department has made of the safety and suitability for house building of military sites in the City of York.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","6368"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754601","Department for International Trade","false","2017-09-07","<p>The value of UK defence exports (based on orders) from 2012 – 2016 is shown in the table below.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£BN</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>8.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>9.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>8.5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>7.7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>5.9</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><em> </em></p><p><em> </em></p><p><em> </em></p><p><em> </em></p><p><em> </em></p><p><em> </em></p><p><em>Source: </em><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/uk-defence-and-security-export-figures-2016" target="_blank"><em>DIT DSO</em></a></p><p><em> </em></p><p>The data is taken from the official statistics based on orders or sales “UK defence and security export figures 2016”. These are compiled annually by the DIT DSO Market Analysis team and are published on the gov.uk website: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/uk-defence-and-security-export-figures-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/uk-defence-and-security-export-figures-2016</a></p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-09-07T10:31:35.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754601/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754601/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754601/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-07-20","Defence Equipment: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what the value was of UK export orders of defence equipment and services in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","6737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754602","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>The Defence People Mental Health and Wellbeing Strategy launched on 20 July is aimed at providing a better focus and use of existing services including welfare support, training and education, anti-stigma campaigns and mental health services provided by Defence Medical Services, the National Health Service in England and the Devolved Administrations and charities. The Strategy is well resourced through connected agencies and services which the forthcoming Mental Health and Wellbeing Strategy Action Plan will take on and develop.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-05T15:08:21.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754602/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754602/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754602/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-20","Armed Forces: Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much funding has been allocated to his Department's Defence People Mental Health and Wellbeing Strategy.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","6735"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754603","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>Information on how much the Ministry of Defence has spent directly on goods and services provided by small and medium-sized enterprises in each of the last five years can be accessed at Table 6a of the excel tables published in the Trade Industry &amp; Contracts Statistical Bulletin, which can be found at the following link:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/mod-trade-industry-and-contracts-2016.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-09-05T15:11:26.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754603/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754603/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754603/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-20","Ministry of Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department spent on goods and services provided by small and medium-sized enterprise in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","6736"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754604","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>Trauma Risk Management (TRiM) training is valid for three years, and the Services operate a continual programme of revalidation and training of new personnel, to allow for staff turnover.</p><p> </p><p>The Royal Navy currently has 1,426 qualified TRiM practitioners, of whom 806 are Team Leaders. The numbers trained in each of the last five full “training years” is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Training Year (April-March)</p></td><td><p>Team Leaders</p></td><td><p>Practitioners</p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>122</p></td><td><p>224</p></td><td><p>346</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>136</p></td><td><p>232</p></td><td><p>368</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>201</p></td><td><p>218</p></td><td><p>419</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>266</p></td><td><p>215</p></td><td><p>481</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>303</p></td><td><p>205</p></td><td><p>508</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Army currently has 1,992 qualified TRiM practitioners, of whom 675 are Co-ordinators (the term used by the Army for Team Leaders). The numbers trained in each of the last five full “training years” is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Training Year (April-March)</p></td><td><p>Co-ordinators/ Team Leaders</p></td><td><p>Practitioners</p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>163</p></td><td><p>522</p></td><td><p>685</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>214</p></td><td><p>586</p></td><td><p>800</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>168</p></td><td><p>643</p></td><td><p>811</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>315</p></td><td><p>714</p></td><td><p>1,029</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>396</p></td><td><p>853</p></td><td><p>1,249</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Royal Air Force currently has 1,826 qualified TRiM practitioners, of whom 367 are Team Leaders. The numbers trained in each of the last five full “training years” is as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Training Year (April-March)</p></td><td><p>Team Leaders</p></td><td><p>Practitioners</p></td><td><p>Total</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>83</p></td><td><p>488</p></td><td><p>571</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>79</p></td><td><p>572</p></td><td><p>651</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>111</p></td><td><p>673</p></td><td><p>784</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>143</p></td><td><p>704</p></td><td><p>847</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>139</p></td><td><p>794</p></td><td><p>933</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-05T15:10:34.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754604/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754604/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754604/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-20","Armed Forces: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many personnel in the (a) Royal Navy, (b) Army and (c) RAF have completed trauma risk management training in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","6734"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754605","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-09-05","<p>The Defence People Mental Health and Wellbeing Strategy will provide a better focus and use of existing services provided by Defence Medical Services, the National Health Service (NHS) in England and the Devolved Administrations and charities. The NHS has primary responsibility for healthcare, including mental healthcare, for former spouses of Service personnel residing in the UK following divorce or separation except those registered with Defence Medical Services. There is no separate provision through the Strategy for former spouses of Service personnel but the Strategy provides the platform for collaborative working with the NHS (including through our commissioning group) to ensure that the needs of former spouses are met in the context of improving mental health under the Five Year Forward view in England.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-09-05T14:11:17.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754605/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754605/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754605/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-07-20","Armed Forces: Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what provision will be made for former spouses of service personnel following divorce or separation as part of his Department's Defence People Mental Health and Wellbeing Strategy.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","6738"
