"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754676","Department for Education","false","2017-09-07","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 5 September 2017 to Questions UIN 5931 and 5933:</p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-07-18/5931/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-07-18/5931/</a>.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","6615 ; 6616 ; 6621","2017-09-07T12:34:25.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754676/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754676/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754676/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-20","Free Schools: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to her oral statement of 17 July 2017, Official Report, column 565, how many of the 30 free schools to be delivered through the local authority route will be built in (a) 2017-18, (b) 2018-19, (c) 2019-20, (d) 2020-21 and (e) 2021-22.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","6617"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754677","Department for Education","false","2017-09-11","<p>This Government believes it is right to maximise the amount of funding which is allocated directly to schools, enabling head teachers, to use their professional expertise to ensure that it is spent where it will have the greatest impact.</p><p>We are looking across all areas of the department’s budget for efficiencies. We will maintain funding on the highest value areas, particularly the Government’s priorities. As part of this process, we have said that we will release £200 million from central programmes that support schools on relatively narrow areas of their work. We will also release £420 million from the Department's capital budget.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","6619 ; 6622 ; 6623 ; 6629 ; 6630 ; 6631","2017-09-11T15:29:35.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754677/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754677/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754677/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-20","Schools: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to her oral statement of 17 July 2017 Official Report, column 565, from which of her Department's programmes the £250 million will be found to finance the  increase in the core schools budget in 2018 - 19.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","6620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754678","Department for Education","false","2017-09-07","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 5 September 2017 to Questions UIN 5931 and 5933:</p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-07-18/5931/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-07-18/5931/</a>.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","6615 ; 6616 ; 6617","2017-09-07T12:34:26.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754678/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754678/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754678/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-20","Free Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to her oral statement of 17 July 2017 Official Report, column 565, what criteria will be used to assess which local authorities will deliver the 30 free schools.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","6621"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754679","Department for Education","false","2017-09-06","<p>To allow us to prioritise core school funding, we have had to make difficult decisions about other budgets. We have, therefore, decided to make savings of £315 million from healthy pupils capital funding.</p><p>We think it is right to maximise the funding that goes directly to all schools, and put decisions about spending in the hands of headteachers who know best how to use their funding to achieve the best outcomes for their pupils. Every pound of England’s share of spending funded by the Soft Drinks Industry Levy will, however, continue to be invested in improving child health, including £100m in 2018-19 on healthy pupils capital.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-09-06T14:03:24.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754679/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754679/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754679/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-20","Schools: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to her oral statement of 17 July 2017, Official Report, column 565, what estimate she has made of the savings to be made from the healthy pupils capital to increase core schools funding in 2018-19.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","6614"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754680","Department for Education","false","2017-09-07","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 5 September 2017 to Questions UIN 5931 and 5933:</p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-07-18/5931/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-07-18/5931/</a>.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","6616 ; 6617 ; 6621","2017-09-07T12:34:25.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754680/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754680/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754680/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-20","Schools: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to her oral statement of 17 July 2017, Official Report, column 565, what estimate she has made of the savings to be made from the free schools budget to increase core schools funding in 2018-19.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","6615"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754681","Department for Education","false","2017-09-07","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 5 September 2017 to Questions UIN 5931 and 5933:</p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-07-18/5931/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2017-07-18/5931/</a>.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","6615 ; 6617 ; 6621","2017-09-07T12:34:25.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754681/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754681/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754681/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-20","Schools: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to her oral statement of 17 July 2017, Official Report, column 565, what estimate she has made of the savings to be made from the free schools budget to increase core schools funding in 2019-20.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","6616"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754683","Department for Education","false","2017-09-11","<p>This Government believes it is right to maximise the amount of funding which is allocated directly to schools, enabling head teachers, to use their professional expertise to ensure that it is spent where it will have the greatest impact.</p><p>We are looking across all areas of the department’s budget for efficiencies. We will maintain funding on the highest value areas, particularly the Government’s priorities. As part of this process, we have said that we will release £200 million from central programmes that support schools on relatively narrow areas of their work. We will also release £420 million from the Department's capital budget.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","6620 ; 6622 ; 6623 ; 6629 ; 6630 ; 6631","2017-09-11T15:29:35.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754683/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754683/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754683/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-20","Schools: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to her oral statement of 17 July 2017 Official Report, column 565, from which programmes the £350 million will be found to finance the increase in core schools budget in 2019 - 20.","false","Biography information for Angela Rayner","Ashton-under-Lyne","Angela Rayner","6619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754684","Department for Education","false","2017-09-06","<p>First teaching of the current curriculum only started in September 2014. The new National Curriculum was developed with input from employers, Further Education and Higher Education representatives. It is designed to equip pupils with the knowledge they need to go on to further education or careers, including in the creative industries.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-09-06T07:30:42.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754684/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754684/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/754684/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-07-20","Curriculum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment her Department has made of the effect of school curriculum changes since 2010 on employment in the creative industries.","false","Biography information for Layla Moran","Oxford West and Abingdon","Layla Moran","6613"
